               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary"> This undated, complete copy of the <title>Taẕkirat
                        al-Shuʻarā</title> (Chronicles of Poets) by Dawlatshāh Samarqandī (d. ca.
                     1494) contains biographical accounts of some 150 poets, together with
                     selections of their works. The author hailed from a ruling Timurid-era elite
                     family and dedicated this work to the cultural and political figure <persName
                        role="dte" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/22198747/" key="person_22198747">Mīr
                        ‘Alī Shīr Navā'ī (d. 1501)</persName>. Probably completed in India, a
                     Scottish bookbinder named <persName key="person_f3538">Robert MacCulloch (fl.
                        1827–1834)</persName> either bound or rebound at his firm in <placeName
                        type="city" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7030776">Mirzapore,
                        Calcutta (Kolkata)</placeName>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_309-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/79263034" key="person_79263034"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Dawlatshāh Samarqandī, d.
                           ca. 1494</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">دولتشاه سمرقندى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20871" change="#ids-cleanup">Taz̲kirat
                        al-shuʻarāʼ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20871" change="#ids-cleanup">تذکرة
                        الشعراء</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus>
                        تحمیدی که شاهباز بلند پرواز اندیشه بساخت و فضای آن نتواند نمود </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="311b" to="311b"> برگ ۳۱۱پ (folio
                           311b):</locus> خدم بتأليف التذكرة أقل العباد دولتشاه بن علا الدولة يحيى
                        شاه الغازي أصلح الله شأنه </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon, and a date of <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                           notBefore="1487" notAfter="1488">892 AH (1487–88 CE)</date> indicates the
                        date of the original work's composition, not completion of this
                        manuscript.</colophon>
                     <note>Former owner <persName type="standard" role="ins fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/" key="person_20108923">Nathaniel
                           Bland</persName> repeatedly references this work in his seminal essay on
                        chronicles of poets, and <persName role="edt"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/29651479/" key="person_29651479">E. G.
                           Browne</persName> published a critical edition in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date>. For other copies in the
                        Rylands collections, see <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7036"><idno>Persian
                              MS 54</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6803">310</ref>,
                        and <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7346"
                           >838</ref>.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
